1
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:38,233
<i> I feel guilty.</i>

2
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:41,800
<i>I can't bear seeing my mom
and siblings crying.</i>

3
00:00:41,933 --> 00:00:44,100
<i> It's all my fault.</i>

4
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:45,700
<i> Instead of blaming yourself,</i>

5
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:48,500
<i>do something to find your
father.</i>

6
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:50,167
<i>What about the van?
The plate number?</i>

7
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:51,833
<i> 43781.</i>

8
00:00:51,967 --> 00:00:53,833
<i> NBF 4?</i>

9
00:00:53,967 --> 00:00:54,933
<i> Let go of me!</i>

10
00:00:55,067 --> 00:00:57,133
<i>Not until you tell me
where my dad is!</i>

11
00:00:57,267 --> 00:01:00,067
<i>- Let go of me!
- I'll fight you, Hazel!</i>

12
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,767
<i>He's harassing me!
He's hurting me!</i>

13
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:03,533
<i>What are you talking about?
She's the one hurting me!</i>

14
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:04,567
<i> I'm not hurting her!</i>

15
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:06,367
<i>I will send you to jail!
You'll go to jail!</i>

16
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:07,800
<i>- Jeffrey, son.
- Mom.</i>

17
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:09,267
<i> Did they hurt you?</i>

18
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:12,400
<i>I don't want to be here, Mom.
Please get me out of here.</i>

19
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:14,267
<i> That woman is the worst.</i>

20
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:16,300
<i>You should file a case against
her, Jeff.</i>

21
00:01:16,433 --> 00:01:17,400
<i> How can I sue her?</i>

22
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:19,733
<i>We don't even know where
the hell she's hiding.</i>

23
00:01:19,867 --> 00:01:21,267
<i> We'll find them, Jeff.</i>

24
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:24,833
<i>Colonel Sarabia already knows
who owns the van</i>

25
00:01:24,967 --> 00:01:26,700
<i>that Hazel used to get Dad away.</i>

26
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:28,367
<i> Manuel? Time to eat.</i>

27
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:30,167
<i>Hazel, why did you bring me
here?</i>

28
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:31,833
<i>To take me away from my family?</i>

29
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:33,067
<i> Eat first.</i>

30
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,467
<i> But you must explain to me</i>

31
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,000
<i>why you took me away from my
family.</i>

32
00:01:39,667 --> 00:01:41,433
<i> Go on and eat.</i>

33
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:48,767
Attorney, can my kids file
a case against Hazel

34
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:52,200
for taking their dad away
from them?

35
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:55,833
Hazel is Manuel's legal wife.

36
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:58,767
And under the Family Code,

37
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,233
she has the authority
to decide on his care.

38
00:02:03,367 --> 00:02:08,767
Unless we can prove that Manuel
was taken against his will.

39
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:13,133
Our dad has just undergone
surgery, Attorney.

40
00:02:13,267 --> 00:02:18,667
We suspect that Hazel forced him
to sign the discharge form.

41
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:21,700
Yeah. Or maybe his signature
was forged.

42
00:02:21,833 --> 00:02:25,433
Well, if your claim is true,

43
00:02:25,567 --> 00:02:28,933
that is grounds for coercion
and falsification.

44
00:02:29,067 --> 00:02:32,433
However, it must be backed up
by solid evidence.

45
00:02:32,567 --> 00:02:35,167
We can't rely on guesses
or suspicions.

46
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:40,467
What we can do is find someone
to testify about Manuel.

47
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,033
Or he can testify himself.

48
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,667
Jessica.

49
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:48,000
But I doubt that she will
cooperate and testify

50
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:49,000
against her mother.

51
00:02:49,133 --> 00:02:49,800
Exactly.

52
00:02:50,967 --> 00:02:53,300
Dad is the only one
who can testify.

53
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:00,767
We don't know where they are.

54
00:03:02,167 --> 00:03:05,100
Then, that's our first move.

55
00:03:05,233 --> 00:03:06,500
We have to locate them.

56
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:10,300
We can file a Missing Persons
Complaint

57
00:03:10,433 --> 00:03:13,467
or ask the local authorities
for help.

58
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:17,367
We can trace the van they used.

59
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:20,733
It could be found
in the traffic CCTVs.

60
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:24,833
In that way, we can track
the location where they went.

61
00:03:24,967 --> 00:03:28,967
Right, Attorney. We're already
having the van traced.

62
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:33,333
Attorney, what can we do if we
find them and prove

63
00:03:34,433 --> 00:03:39,933
that Manuel was taken out of the
hospital against his will?

64
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:43,033
We can file a Petition
for Habeas Corpus.

65
00:03:43,167 --> 00:03:49,167
Meaning, the court will order
Hazel to bring him out.

66
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:54,233
She has to prove that she's not
hiding Manuel unlawfully.

67
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,733
Right now,
I'd like to reiterate.

68
00:03:56,867 --> 00:03:59,167
We need solid evidence.

69
00:04:00,267 --> 00:04:02,300
So we can move forward.

70
00:04:02,433 --> 00:04:05,600
Alright, Attorney.
Let's find them.

71
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:11,967
And once we prove that Hazel
put Manuel's life in danger,

72
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:15,733
she'll answer for what she did.

73
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:31,700
There.

74
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,733
Here's more.

75
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:42,400
Here's more.

76
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:46,867
There you go.

77
00:04:48,367 --> 00:04:53,467
The doctor advised me to bring
you to a quiet place,

78
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,500
away from stress.

79
00:04:55,633 --> 00:04:59,467
That's why I brought you here
to the province.

80
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:02,467
You'll recover quickly here.

81
00:05:02,633 --> 00:05:05,500
There's fresh air,
and it's peaceful.

82
00:05:07,167 --> 00:05:07,833
Here.

83
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,267
I don't understand.

84
00:05:14,533 --> 00:05:18,533
Why does it feel heavy? And...

85
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:23,100
why do I feel sleepy?
I just woke up.

86
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:25,967
It's okay.

87
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,867
It's the medicine taking effect.

88
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,600
Don't worry, I'll massage you
later.

89
00:05:30,733 --> 00:05:32,233
So you can feel more
comfortable.

90
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:34,367
Eat some more.

91
00:05:36,033 --> 00:05:37,400
It's okay.

92
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:39,000
I'm already full.

93
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:41,267
Manuel, you haven't eaten much.

94
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:44,500
- Come on. One more bite.
- I'm full.

95
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:45,567
No.

96
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,467
Okay.

97
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:51,833
Take your medicines.

98
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:00,133
Here.

99
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:03,600
Manuel.

100
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:07,267
Take your medicines.

101
00:06:08,567 --> 00:06:09,733
Manuel.

102
00:06:09,867 --> 00:06:10,667
There you go.

103
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:21,100
One more, Manuel.

104
00:06:31,233 --> 00:06:33,733
I'm not taking you away
from anyone.

105
00:06:36,567 --> 00:06:37,700
You know.

106
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:44,000
Even though it hurts,
I told Felma where we are.

107
00:06:45,367 --> 00:06:47,467
She knows where we are, Manuel.

108
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:00,867
Yes, Colonel Sarabia.

109
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,200
We'll wait for it. Thank you.

110
00:07:15,633 --> 00:07:19,067
<i>Once the kids have forgiven me,
I'll bring back the joy,</i>

111
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:21,700
<i>the laughter, and the peace we
once had.</i>

112
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,267
<i> I'll get better, Felma.</i>

113
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:27,367
<i>I'll do everything
to walk again.</i>

114
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:30,633
<i>Because it's my dream to walk
you down the aisle</i>

115
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:32,667
<i> without my wheelchair.</i>

116
00:07:36,133 --> 00:07:38,067
They have already forgiven you,
Manuel.

117
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:46,600
So keep your promise.

118
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,333
Get well soon.

119
00:07:57,367 --> 00:07:58,800
Please call me.

120
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:03,100
Come home.

121
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:09,167
We're waiting for you.

122
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:11,133
I'm waiting for you.

123
00:08:16,667 --> 00:08:18,133
Please don't cry.

124
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,933
We will find Dad.

125
00:08:23,367 --> 00:08:24,833
He'll come home, Mom.

126
00:08:39,967 --> 00:08:41,733
Don't cry, Dear.

127
00:08:43,467 --> 00:08:45,733
We'll find your dad.

128
00:08:59,333 --> 00:08:59,933
- This is for you, Ma'am.
- Thank you.

129
00:09:00,067 --> 00:09:01,367
Ma'am, can you please sign here?

130
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,000
- Thank you, Ma'am.
- Thank you.

131
00:09:10,933 --> 00:09:13,567
We'll now find out
who owns the van.

132
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:32,367
This is not the car,

133
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,267
but they have the same plate
number.

134
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:38,500
Colonel Sarabia has a note, Sis.

135
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:45,167
Felma, Andrea, the real owner
of this plate number

136
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:47,200
is a victim of plate cloning.

137
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:48,967
His record is clean.

138
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:51,167
His case is being investigated

139
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:53,467
by the Road Transportation
Agency

140
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,000
along with many other cases
of plate cloning.

141
00:09:57,533 --> 00:10:04,700
That means the van Hazel rented
is doing shady business.

142
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:06,667
Hazel really is cunning.

143
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:09,200
She behaves like a criminal.

144
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:11,667
So we're back to zero.

145
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:14,233
Are we still going to find Dad?

146
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:17,633
Don't worry, Coleen.

147
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:19,367
We'll find a way.

148
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:21,667
Until when?

149
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:24,667
What if Hazel beats us to it?

150
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,733
What if he manages to get Dad
back into Canada illegally?

151
00:10:27,867 --> 00:10:29,067
No.

152
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,233
She can't do that.

153
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,600
If that happens...

154
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,367
Lord, please don't let it
happen. I'm begging you.

155
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:40,133
I'd like to ask for Dad's
forgiveness.

156
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:44,133
I want to tell him I regret
everything.

157
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:48,167
I want to tell him
I love him so much.

158
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:51,133
Lord, please.

159
00:10:51,267 --> 00:10:54,133
- I won't bear it, Jeff.
- That's enough.

160
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:56,267
That's enough.

161
00:11:04,033 --> 00:11:05,867
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

162
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:09,833
Why didn't you answer
my question sooner?

163
00:11:11,367 --> 00:11:16,133
Because I want you to see me.

164
00:11:17,433 --> 00:11:19,033
Me first, Manuel.

165
00:11:20,367 --> 00:11:21,400
Only me.

166
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,800
I'm the one in front of you.

167
00:11:25,967 --> 00:11:26,967
I want...

168
00:11:28,767 --> 00:11:33,100
you to see how sorry I am.

169
00:11:35,133 --> 00:11:36,833
That I've changed.

170
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:39,767
I want you to see my love.

171
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:42,833
Hazel,

172
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:47,333
since we got married,

173
00:11:48,767 --> 00:11:51,333
I've tried my best to look
at you.

174
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:57,000
But I never saw any love.

175
00:11:59,067 --> 00:12:04,700
Just constant abuse
and humiliation.

176
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:09,000
Manuel, look at me again.

177
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:12,800
Look at me again.

178
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:15,767
You'll see a different me.

179
00:12:17,133 --> 00:12:19,733
I'll give you nothing but love.

180
00:12:22,233 --> 00:12:24,500
Hazel, I will never see that.

181
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,300
Why?

182
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:31,267
Is it because of Felma?

183
00:12:34,167 --> 00:12:35,167
Yes.

184
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:43,300
But it's also because of you.

185
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:48,500
Back when I was able,
you never managed to love me.

186
00:12:49,633 --> 00:12:51,567
How much more now?

187
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:08,333
Manuel,

188
00:13:09,633 --> 00:13:12,000
don't I have the right
to change?

189
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:19,367
Why do you think I still want
to get back together with you?

190
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:23,767
Because I love you.

191
00:13:25,533 --> 00:13:27,033
I love you so much.

192
00:13:28,667 --> 00:13:31,000
Hazel, that's not love.

193
00:13:33,467 --> 00:13:36,167
You see me as nothing
but your possession.

194
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:40,467
Belonging to you,
and only you can have me.

195
00:13:42,967 --> 00:13:44,733
Manuel, that's not true.

196
00:13:44,867 --> 00:13:46,900
That's not true.

197
00:13:47,033 --> 00:13:49,600
Hazel, that's the truth.

198
00:13:49,733 --> 00:13:53,567
Hazel, just let me go.

199
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,233
I know what you're doing.

200
00:14:00,933 --> 00:14:02,733
You're trying to get me mad.

201
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:07,633
You want the old Hazel
to come out.

202
00:14:09,867 --> 00:14:12,100
Manuel, that's not going
to happen.

203
00:14:14,867 --> 00:14:20,200
You can get mad at me every day,
yell at me.

204
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:21,700
I'll accept it.

205
00:14:22,833 --> 00:14:24,133
I'll accept it, Manuel.

206
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:26,833
Because I love you.

207
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:30,867
So much.

208
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:34,267
- I love you so much, Manuel.
- Hazel, please stop.

209
00:14:36,067 --> 00:14:37,267
Stop.

210
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:41,533
I'm begging you.

211
00:14:41,667 --> 00:14:44,833
I don't believe you anymore.

212
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:49,633
And I don't love you anymore.

213
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:55,833
Honestly, I tried to love you,

214
00:14:57,067 --> 00:14:57,867
yet...

215
00:14:59,767 --> 00:15:02,767
you're the one who made it
impossible for me to love you.

216
00:15:02,933 --> 00:15:04,533
So, please.

217
00:15:04,667 --> 00:15:09,333
Please let me go.
Give me back my phone.

218
00:15:09,467 --> 00:15:11,933
Let me talk to Felma.

219
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:16,967
Please, Hazel.

220
00:15:23,967 --> 00:15:25,033
Hazel.

221
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:40,200
I don't have your cellphone

222
00:15:41,233 --> 00:15:43,133
or wheelchair.

223
00:15:43,267 --> 00:15:44,767
Felma has them.

224
00:15:46,167 --> 00:15:47,467
But don't worry.

225
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:54,667
I asked them to bring them
when they visit you next week.

226
00:15:57,533 --> 00:15:58,967
Next week, Manuel.

227
00:16:01,033 --> 00:16:01,900
Yes,

228
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:06,867
I'm willing to sacrifice
for you.

229
00:16:09,167 --> 00:16:10,133
No, Hazel.

230
00:16:11,267 --> 00:16:12,500
I don't want to wait
for next week.

231
00:16:12,633 --> 00:16:14,900
I'd like to talk to Felma now.

232
00:16:15,033 --> 00:16:17,367
Hazel, give me your phone.

233
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,000
Give it to me.

234
00:16:20,133 --> 00:16:22,200
There's no signal here.

235
00:16:22,333 --> 00:16:23,100
Come on.

236
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,700
Give me your phone.

237
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:40,900
Manuel.

238
00:16:42,633 --> 00:16:44,133
Manuel, you can't move yet.

239
00:16:44,267 --> 00:16:45,200
Wait.

240
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:48,900
Manuel, there's no signal here.

241
00:16:49,033 --> 00:16:50,400
Bring me outside.

242
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:54,133
Manuel, you can't handle it yet.

243
00:16:54,267 --> 00:16:56,267
You can't go out yet, Manuel.

244
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:59,000
Manuel, don't be stubborn!

245
00:16:59,133 --> 00:17:00,067
Manuel!

246
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:02,733
Manuel.

247
00:17:02,867 --> 00:17:03,833
Look.

248
00:17:03,967 --> 00:17:07,967
You're not ready yet.
Manuel, no. Stay there.

249
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:08,600
Manuel.

250
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:13,600
Manuel.

251
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:18,100
Manuel, please be more patient.
Okay?

252
00:17:18,267 --> 00:17:19,433
Please be more patient.

253
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:25,967
I don't get it, Hazel.

254
00:17:28,700 --> 00:17:31,067
Why is this happening to me?

255
00:17:34,967 --> 00:17:37,667
Is it not enough
that I'm disabled?

256
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,667
That my legs are disabled?

257
00:17:43,233 --> 00:17:46,267
Which part of me hasn't been
hurt yet?

258
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:48,867
What else?

259
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:51,967
Manuel.

260
00:17:55,167 --> 00:17:57,833
Manuel, please stop.
That's enough.

261
00:18:00,567 --> 00:18:01,933
Hang in there, okay?

262
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:06,467
Please endure it a little more.

263
00:18:18,667 --> 00:18:20,633
<i> You're doing right, Manuel.</i>

264
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:22,400
<i> Just hold on to me.</i>

265
00:18:23,567 --> 00:18:27,767
<i>Whatever attitude you throw
at me, I won't give up on you.</i>

266
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:30,567
<i> You can never push me away.</i>

267
00:18:31,733 --> 00:18:35,200
<i>I'll give you a care
you can't refuse.</i>

268
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:41,033
<i>I'll do everything
until you forget Felma</i>

269
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:43,267
<i> and choose me in the end.</i>

270
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:54,667
<i>I'm sorry, the subscriber cannot
be reached.</i>

271
00:18:57,067 --> 00:19:01,000
Ma'am, I can't reach Jessica
anymore.

272
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:05,133
It looks like her evil mom
confiscated her phone.

273
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:11,567
But don't you have any idea
where they are?

274
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:14,133
Didang, I don't.

275
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:19,867
We thought the plate number
of the van

276
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,833
Hazel used could help
to track them.

277
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,567
Turns out, it's fake.

278
00:19:25,933 --> 00:19:29,033
Speaking of Hazel, Ma'am...

279
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:31,100
Have you tried calling her?

280
00:19:31,233 --> 00:19:33,500
You know her number, right?

281
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,333
Manuel,

282
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:02,000
how are you doing?

283
00:20:06,367 --> 00:20:08,867
I feel better now.

284
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:12,733
Thank you, Hazel.

285
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,733
What's ringing?

286
00:20:29,733 --> 00:20:31,067
It's ringing.

287
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:34,000
Hazel.

288
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:40,300
It's ringing.

289
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:44,267
There's none.

290
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,567
Nothing's ringing, Manuel.

291
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:49,833
Maybe it's a side effect
of the medicine.

292
00:20:49,967 --> 00:20:53,600
Ringing sounds are normal.

293
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:58,567
Get some rest for now.

294
00:21:11,067 --> 00:21:12,567
It just keeps ringing.

295
00:21:15,767 --> 00:21:20,167
Why did we even expect her
to answer?

296
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:23,833
Ma'am, don't stop.
Keep calling her.

297
00:21:23,967 --> 00:21:26,533
She'll get irritated
and take your call.

298
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,300
She's rejecting it.

299
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:15,933
Hazel,

300
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:18,667
where's Manuel?

301
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:22,667
Manuel? My husband?

302
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:26,567
The man you're obsessed
with from head to toe?

303
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:28,100
He's here.

304
00:22:28,233 --> 00:22:31,033
He's sleeping soundly. Look.

305
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:35,900
Manuel.

306
00:22:41,633 --> 00:22:45,533
Hazel, bring him back
to the hospital.

307
00:22:45,667 --> 00:22:47,967
Bring him back
to the hospital.

308
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:50,367
He's not ready
for what he's in right now.

309
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:54,167
Don't worry.

310
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:57,867
Nothing bad will happen to him
as long as he's with me.

311
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:02,400
Have mercy on Manuel.
Think about his safety.

312
00:23:02,533 --> 00:23:04,233
What do you want to happen,
Felma?

313
00:23:04,367 --> 00:23:06,433
Bring him back to the hospital

314
00:23:06,567 --> 00:23:09,400
so you and your illegitimate
kids can visit him anytime?

315
00:23:09,533 --> 00:23:12,167
Hey, that will never happen.

316
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:13,500
And guess what?

317
00:23:13,633 --> 00:23:22,700
You will never see Manuel again
because I'm the only Mrs. Cruz.

318
00:23:22,867 --> 00:23:27,300
I'm the only
Mrs. Hazel Capistrano-Cruz.

319
00:23:39,633 --> 00:23:43,000
Manuel. You're a monster, Hazel.

320
00:23:43,133 --> 00:23:45,700
You really are a monster!

321
00:23:45,833 --> 00:23:49,900
Monster!

322
00:23:50,033 --> 00:23:59,100
Manuel!

323
00:23:59,267 --> 00:24:02,100
You're a monster, Hazel!

324
00:24:02,233 --> 00:24:04,867
Monster!

325
00:24:46,667 --> 00:24:47,800
Come on, charge.

326
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:08,333
Are you looking for this?

327
00:25:11,633 --> 00:25:12,433
Mom.

328
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:15,300
Mom.

329
00:25:17,867 --> 00:25:20,033
- Mom...
- Who are you going to call?

330
00:25:20,167 --> 00:25:21,733
- Mom!
- Are you going to call Felma?

331
00:25:24,767 --> 00:25:27,900
I really hate that evil Hazel.
But I hope...

332
00:25:28,033 --> 00:25:31,133
Jessica's there. I'm sure she'll
take care of Dad.

333
00:25:31,267 --> 00:25:32,667
Are we still going to see Dad?

334
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,567
I wonder how he's doing.

335
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:36,233
How are you getting
by these days?

336
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:41,567
I used my acting skills
to manipulate the Wilsons.

337
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:43,633
I took a picture of Manuel
in the ICU.

338
00:25:43,767 --> 00:25:45,133
The couple felt so sorry
for him.

339
00:25:45,267 --> 00:25:46,467
They even doubled it.

340
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:48,167
You're embarrassing, Mom.

341
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:49,200
What did you say?

342
00:25:49,333 --> 00:25:50,400
Hold on.

343
00:25:52,167 --> 00:25:53,033
Someone texted.

344
00:25:54,433 --> 00:25:56,400
I know where Manuel Cruz is.

345
00:25:56,533 --> 00:25:58,267
Are you sure you know
where my father is?

346
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,667
I'm one of the people
who brought him there.

347
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:00,867
Where did you bring my father?

348
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:01,933
Let's meet.

349
00:26:02,067 --> 00:26:05,433
Mom is so happy taking care
of you, Dad.

350
00:26:05,567 --> 00:26:10,200
Don't you realize that Mom
and I are your family?

351
00:26:10,367 --> 00:26:14,500
No, Dear. I want to get better.

352
00:26:14,633 --> 00:26:18,067
So I can file the annulment
of my marriage to Hazel.
